description: From Latin suffumigatus, past participle of suffumigare (“to fumigate from below”). See sub-, and fumigate.

verbs.description: suffumigate (third-person singular simple present suffumigates, present participle suffumigating, simple past and past participle suffumigated)

entries.meaning: To apply fumes or smoke to the parts of, as to the body in medicine; to fumigate in part.
